“Self-acclaimed” African Giant, Burna Boy has dropped some words to keep his fans well motivated. In a recent Twitter post, the Afrobeats super star told his fans to eliminate ‘regret’ from their vocabulary.   Naira Marley asks fans if they will vote him as president     Wizkid laughs off Banky W’s interview     EmmCee RNB releases new single ahead of debut project   Burna Boy urged them to keep striving at being better, make mistakes if they have to but never regret. Odogwu added instead of being regretful about mistakes, people should rather learn from them as no one is ever perfect. Burna wrote: “NO REGRETS. Keep working, keep Trying, keep Moving. Make mistakes and learn but NEVER REGRET. I ain’t perfect neither are you. Nobody is.”